-- AGL Energy May Add Merrill to Its Advisory Team, Financial Review Reports
-- B y   E l i s a b e t h   B e h r m a n n
-- 2010-10-07T20:33:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/agl-energy-may-add-merrill-to-its-advisory-team-financial-review-reports.html
AGL Energy Ltd. is considering adding
Bank of America unit Merrill Lynch to its advisory team ahead of
the Nov. 1 deadline for bids in New South Wales’ A$8
billion electricity auction, the Australian Financial Review
reported in its Street Talk column without naming anyone. AGL’s
current advisors include Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc and
Citigroup Inc, the report said. Likely bidders for the assets
include Origin Energy Ltd. and TRUenergy Holdings Pty Ltd.,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisabeth Behrmann in Sydney at 
